📊 Random Variable and Variable

* Variable
A characteristic that can take different values.
Example: Age, Marks, Height.

* Random Variable
A variable whose value depends on the outcome of a random experiment.

🔹 Types

1. Discrete Random Variable → Countable values.
Example: Number of heads in 3 coin tosses.

2. Continuous Random Variable → Any value within a range.
Example: Height, weight, temperature.

🖼️ Diagram
Variable
 ├── Quantitative
 │    ├── Discrete
 │    └── Continuous
 └── Qualitative (Categorical)
